There are basically three ways
we can interact with Git.

00:00:03.465 --> 00:00:04.860
We can either use gets

00:00:04.860 --> 00:00:10.770
CMD or Git Bash or get GUI
or graphical user interface.

00:00:10.770 --> 00:00:12.870
Gets CMV is nothing but

00:00:12.870 --> 00:00:16.695
the Windows command processor
we use to run git commands.

00:00:16.695 --> 00:00:18.510
In fact, we had already
taken a look at

00:00:18.510 --> 00:00:21.285
an example of the same
in our previous lecture,

00:00:21.285 --> 00:00:24.345
where we were testing the
installation of getting.

00:00:24.345 --> 00:00:28.740
The other option we have
is to use Git Bash,

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:31.920
which is a tool we had
installed along with Git.

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:35.500
Git Bash is similar to
Windows command processor,

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:37.115
except that we can use

00:00:37.115 --> 00:00:40.385
standard Linux commands
to interact with good.

00:00:40.385 --> 00:00:42.425
This will come in handy,

00:00:42.425 --> 00:00:44.105
especially if you're coming from

00:00:44.105 --> 00:00:46.220
Linux background where you're

00:00:46.220 --> 00:00:48.140
