operating system.

00:00:52.145 --> 00:00:54.770
You don't have to take that
additional learning curve to

00:00:54.770 --> 00:00:58.670
understand Windows command in
order to interact with Git.

00:00:58.670 --> 00:01:01.640
For example, in order to
list down all the files in

00:01:01.640 --> 00:01:05.120
a particular folder inside
Windows command line,

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:07.355
use the command there.

00:01:07.355 --> 00:01:09.770
Whereas in Linux, you use

00:01:09.770 --> 00:01:13.205
